{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883601744,"sessionID":"ses_285178ea0ffepODHz0C64Ihxdr","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae8a773001JEZgnMNQQH8q0o","messageID":"msg_d7ae8812f001X9EW6CmzSrkHia","sessionID":"ses_285178ea0ffepODHz0C64Ihxdr","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_b4b1642983f44620868a28ba","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Delta Specification (AR-040)\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec adds test-focused scenarios and edge cases for the Python SDK testing requirement (AR-040) in the `sdk-python/tests` module.\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient instantiation and configuration\n\n### Scenario: Client initialization with all parameters\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with explicit values for all parameters\n- **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL have `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose`, and `session_id` set to the provided values\n\n### Scenario: Client initialization with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with no arguments\n- **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n- **THEN** `name` SHALL be `\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace` SHALL be `\"default\"`, `ttl` SHALL be `3600`, and `verbose` SHALL be `False`\n\n### Scenario: Router URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set to `\"http://router.example.com\"`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated without `router_url`\n- **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL equal `\"http://router.example.com\"`\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient context manager behavior\n\n### Scenario: Context manager entry creates session\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` is valid and control plane is reachable\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` enters context manager\n- **THEN** `create_session` SHALL be called on the control plane client and `session_id` SHALL be populated\n\n### Scenario: Context manager exit cleans up on success\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` was created with a new session (not provided)\n- **WHEN** the context block exits without exception\n- **THEN** `stop()` SHALL delete the session and close both control plane and data plane clients\n\n### Scenario: Context manager exit cleans up on exception\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` was created with a new session\n- **WHEN** an exception is raised inside the context block\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL still call `stop()` to clean up resources\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: ControlPlaneClient configuration\n\n### Scenario: Control plane URL from argument\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url=\"http://wm.example.com\"` is passed\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal `\"http://wm.example.com\"`\n\n### Scenario: Control plane URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var is set to `\"http://wm.env.com\"` and no argument is passed\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal `\"http://wm.env.com\"`\n\n### Scenario: Control plane authorization with token file\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided and service account token exists at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be set to `\"Bearer {token_content}\"`\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient URL construction\n\n### Scenario: Data plane URL constructed from router components\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"test-ns\"`, `cr_name=\"my-cr\"`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` initializes without `base_url`\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal `\"http://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/test-ns/code-interpreters/my-cr/invocations/\"`\n\n### Scenario: Data plane URL uses explicit base_url\n- **GIVEN** `base_url=\"http://explicit.example.com/v1/namespaces/ns/cr/invocations/\"`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal the provided `base_url`\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: CodeInterpreterClient file operations\n\n### Scenario: write_file sends base64 content\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is configured with valid session\n- **WHEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** a POST request SHALL be made to `api/files` with JSON body containing base64-encoded `content`, `path`, and `mode`\n\n### Scenario: upload_file sends multipart request\n- **GIVEN** a temporary file exists at `/tmp/upload_test.txt`\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/tmp/upload_test.txt\", remote_path=\"/tmp/dest.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** a multipart POST request SHALL be made to `api/files` with file data and path in form fields\n\n### Scenario: download_file streams response\n- **GIVEN** a file exists on the remote at `/tmp/remote.txt`\n- **WHEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/tmp/remote.txt\", local_path=\"/tmp/local.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** a GET request SHALL be made to `api/files/remote.txt` with `stream=True`\n\n### Scenario: list_files queries directory\n- **GIVEN** a directory `/code` exists on the remote\n- **WHEN** `list_files(path=\"/code\")` is called\n- **THEN** a GET request SHALL be made to `api/files?path=%2Fcode`\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient session bootstrap\n\n### Scenario: Session ID extracted from response header\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` makes a GET request to the invocation URL\n- **WHEN** the response includes header `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123`\n- **THEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n\n### Scenario: Missing session header raises error\n- **GIVEN** the GET request to the invocation URL returns without `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: AgentRuntimeClient invoke behavior\n\n### Scenario: Invoke without session raises\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"test\": \"data\"})` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n### Scenario: Invoke sends JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** a valid session_id is set\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"query\": \"test\"})` is called\n- **THEN** a POST request SHALL be made with `Content-Type: application/json` and body containing the payload\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: Exception handling\n\n### Scenario: CommandExecutionError contains exit code and stderr\n- **GIVEN** a command returns exit code `1` with stderr `\"command not found\"`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code=1`, `stderr=\"command not found\"`, and the command in the message\n\n### Scenario: Exception classes are importable\n- **GIVEN** the `agentcube` package is installed\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube import exceptions` is executed\n- **THEN** `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` SHALL be accessible\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: Utility functions\n\n### Scenario: create_session returns requests.Session\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called\n- **WHEN** the function completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` object with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for http and https\n\n### Scenario: read_token_from_file handles missing file\n- **GIVEN** a file path that does not exist\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/path\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return an empty string `\"\"` (not raise)\n\n### Scenario: read_token_from_file returns stripped content\n- **GIVEN** a file exists at `/tmp/token` with content `\"  my-token\\n\"`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-token\"`\n\n### Scenario: get_logger returns Logger instance\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"test_logger\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the function completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance with name `\"test_logger\"`\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: Public API surface\n\n### Scenario: Root package exports CodeInterpreterClient\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL succeed\n\n### Scenario: Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL succeed\n\n### Scenario: Root package __all__ contains correct items\n- **GIVEN** the `agentcube` package\n- **WHEN** `agentcube.__all__` is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n\n---\n\n## Test Requirement: Timeout behavior\n\n### Scenario: Default timeouts are applied\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is instantiated without timeout arguments\n- **WHEN** the client is examined\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n\n### Scenario: Per-call timeout overrides instance timeout\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` has default timeout of 120\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"ls\", timeout=60)` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL use the 60-second timeout for the read timeout\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775883601733,"end":1775883601741}}}}
