{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883705635,"sessionID":"ses_285178ea0ffepODHz0C64Ihxdr","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9b59f001PR5oFnCopAk12T","messageID":"msg_d7ae99760001hbWZeApQhTU2cj","sessionID":"ses_285178ea0ffepODHz0C64Ihxdr","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_5ccf954fef844bb6a4d71e96","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for testing the Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) and its CLI functionality.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-040\n- **Module**: `sdk-python/tests`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n## Reference\n\nBase specs from:\n- `python-sdk/design.md` - SDK design and architecture\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` - Functional requirements\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe Python SDK provides two main client classes:\n- `CodeInterpreterClient`: Manages Code Interpreter sessions via Workload Manager (control plane) and Router (data plane)\n- `AgentRuntimeClient`: Invokes AgentRuntime workloads through the Router\n\nThe SDK also includes utility modules and exception classes.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Feature: CodeInterpreterClient Lifecycle\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-001-A — Client initialization with all parameters\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with explicit values for all parameters\n- **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL have `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `router_url`, `auth_token`, `verbose`, and `session_id` set to the provided values\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-001-B — Client initialization with defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with no arguments\n- **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n- **THEN** `name` SHALL be `\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace` SHALL be `\"default\"`, `ttl` SHALL be `3600`, and `verbose` SHALL be `False`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-001-C — Router URL from environment variable\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set to `\"http://router.example.com\"`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated without `router_url` argument\n- **THEN** `self.router_url` SHALL equal `\"http://router.example.com\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-001-D — Router URL missing raises error\n\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` argument nor `ROUTER_URL` environment variable is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-001-E — Context manager entry creates session\n\n- **GIVEN** `router_url` is valid and control plane is reachable\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` enters context manager (`__enter__`)\n- **THEN** `create_session` SHALL be called on the control plane client\n- **AND** `session_id` SHALL be populated on the instance\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-001-F — Context manager exit cleans up on success\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` was created with a new session (not provided)\n- **WHEN** the context block exits without exception\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()` to delete the session\n- **AND** close both control plane and data plane clients\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-001-G — Context manager exit cleans up on exception\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` was created with a new session\n- **WHEN** an exception is raised inside the context block\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL still call `stop()` to clean up resources\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-001-H — Data plane init failure cleans up session\n\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning\n- **AND** call `delete_session(session_id)`\n- **AND** set `session_id` to `None`\n- **AND** re-raise the exception\n\n---\n\n### Feature: CodeInterpreterClient Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-002-A — Execute command delegates to data plane\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` has a valid `dp_client` (data plane)\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"ls -la\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL delegate to `self.dp_client.execute_command()`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-002-B — Execute command with custom timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` with default timeout 120\n- **WHEN** `execute_command(\"echo test\", timeout=60)` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL use 60-second timeout\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-002-C — Run code for Python writes file and executes\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file`\n- **AND** execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-002-D — Run code normalizes language variants\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance\n- **WHEN** `run_code(\"py\", \"code\")` is called (language \"py\")\n- **THEN** it SHALL treat it the same as \"python\"\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-002-E — File operations delegate to data plane\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` has a valid `dp_client`\n- **WHEN** `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, or `list_files` is called\n- **THEN** each SHALL delegate to the corresponding `dp_client` method\n\n---\n\n### Feature: ControlPlaneClient Configuration\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-003-A — Control plane URL from argument\n\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url=\"http://wm.example.com\"` is passed\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal `\"http://wm.example.com\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-003-B — Control plane URL from environment\n\n- **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var is set and no argument is passed\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal the environment variable value\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-003-C — Control plane authorization with explicit token\n\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token=\"my-token\"` is provided\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.session.headers[\"Authorization\"]` SHALL be set to `\"Bearer my-token\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-003-D — Control plane authorization from token file\n\n- **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided and service account token exists\n- **WHEN** `ControlPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** it SHALL read token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n- **AND** set `Authorization: Bearer {token_content}` header\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-003-E — Control plane default timeout values\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is instantiated without timeout arguments\n- **WHEN** the client is examined\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120`\n- **AND** `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n- **AND** `self.pool_connections` SHALL be `10`\n- **AND** `self.pool_maxsize` SHALL be `10`\n\n---\n\n### Feature: ControlPlaneClient Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-004-A — Create session POSTs to correct endpoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` with `base_url=\"http://wm.example.com\"`\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=3600)` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL POST to `http://wm.example.com/v1/code-interpreter`\n- **AND** JSON body SHALL contain `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`\n- **AND** return the `sessionId` from response\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-004-B — Create session with metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient`\n- **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", metadata={\"key\": \"value\"}, ttl=3600)` is called\n- **THEN** the JSON body SHALL include `metadata` field\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-004-C — Create session missing sessionId raises\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` and successful HTTP response without `sessionId`\n- **WHEN** `create_session` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-004-D — Delete session returns True on 404\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient`\n- **WHEN** `delete_session(\"non-existent-id\")` is called\n- **AND** server returns HTTP 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-004-E — Delete session returns False on other errors\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient`\n- **WHEN** `delete_session(\"some-id\")` is called\n- **AND** server returns HTTP 500\n- **THEN** the method SHALL log the error\n- **AND** return `False`\n\n---\n\n### Feature: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient URL Construction\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-005-A — Data plane URL from router components\n\n- **GIVEN** `router_url=\"http://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"test-ns\"`, `cr_name=\"my-cr\"`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` initializes without `base_url`\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal `\"http://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/test-ns/code-interpreters/my-cr/invocations/\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-005-B — Data plane URL uses explicit base_url\n\n- **GIVEN** `base_url=\"http://explicit.example.com/v1/...\"`\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL equal the provided `base_url`\n\n---\n\n### Feature: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient File Operations\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-006-A — write_file sends base64 content\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with valid session\n- **WHEN** `write_file(content=\"hello world\", remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** a POST request SHALL be made to `api/files`\n- **AND** JSON body SHALL contain base64-encoded `content`, `path`, and `mode: \"0644\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-006-B — upload_file sends multipart request\n\n- **GIVEN** a temporary file exists at `/tmp/upload_test.txt`\n- **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path=\"/tmp/upload_test.txt\", remote_path=\"/tmp/dest.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** a multipart POST request SHALL be made to `api/files`\n- **AND** the request SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-006-C — download_file streams response\n\n- **GIVEN** a file exists on the remote at `/tmp/remote.txt`\n- **WHEN** `download_file(remote_path=\"/tmp/remote.txt\", local_path=\"/tmp/local.txt\")` is called\n- **THEN** a GET request SHALL be made to `api/files/remote.txt`\n- **AND** `stream=True` SHALL be used\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-006-D — list_files queries directory\n\n- **GIVEN** a directory `/code` exists on the remote\n- **WHEN** `list_files(path=\"/code\")` is called\n- **THEN** a GET request SHALL be made to `api/files?path=%2Fcode`\n\n---\n\n### Feature: AgentRuntimeClient Session Bootstrap\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-007-A — AgentRuntimeClient initializes with parameters\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated\n- **WHEN** `__init__` runs\n- **THEN** instance SHALL have `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`, `router_url` set\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-007-B — Session ID extracted from response header\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` makes GET request to invocation URL\n- **WHEN** the response includes header `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123`\n- **THEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` SHALL return `\"abc-123\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-007-C — Missing session header raises error\n\n- **GIVEN** the GET request returns without `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n- **WHEN** `bootstrap_session_id()` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-007-D — Context manager cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits\n- **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n\n---\n\n### Feature: AgentRuntimeClient Invoke\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-008-A — Invoke without session raises\n\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` is `None` or empty\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"query\": \"test\"})` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-008-B — Invoke sends JSON payload\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid session_id is set\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"query\": \"test\"})` is called\n- **THEN** a POST request SHALL be made to the invocation URL\n- **AND** `Content-Type: application/json` header SHALL be set\n- **AND** body SHALL contain the payload as JSON\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-008-C — Invoke uses timeout tuple\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with `timeout=120` and `connect_timeout=5.0`\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={...})` is called without timeout argument\n- **THEN** the request SHALL use timeout `(5.0, 120)`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-008-D — Invoke with per-call timeout override\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` with default timeout 120\n- **WHEN** `invoke(payload={...}, timeout=60)` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL use timeout `(connect_timeout, 60)`\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Exception Handling\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-009-A — CommandExecutionError contains details\n\n- **GIVEN** a command returns exit code `1` with stderr `\"command not found\"`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError`\n- **AND** `exit_code` attribute SHALL be `1`\n- **AND** `stderr` attribute SHALL be `\"command not found\"`\n- **AND** `command` attribute SHALL contain the executed command\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-009-B — Exception classes are importable from root\n\n- **GIVEN** the `agentcube` package is installed\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube import AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError` is executed\n- **THEN** all exception classes SHALL be accessible\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-009-C — Exception classes in exceptions module\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube.exceptions` is imported\n- **WHEN** the module is examined\n- **THEN** `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` SHALL be defined\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Utility Functions\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-010-A — create_session returns requests.Session\n\n- **GIVEN** `create_session()` is called\n- **WHEN** the function completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` object\n- **AND** `HTTPAdapter` SHALL be mounted for http and https\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-010-B — read_token_from_file handles missing file\n\n- **GIVEN** a file path that does not exist\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/nonexistent/path\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return an empty string `\"\"`\n- **AND** NOT raise an exception\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-010-C — read_token_from_file returns stripped content\n\n- **GIVEN** a file exists at `/tmp/token` with content `\"  my-token\\n\"`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file(\"/tmp/token\")` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `\"my-token\"` (whitespace stripped)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-010-D — get_logger returns Logger instance\n\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"test_logger\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the function completes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `logging.Logger` instance\n- **AND** logger name SHALL be `\"test_logger\"`\n\n---\n\n### Feature: Public API Surface\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-011-A — Root package exports CodeInterpreterClient\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-011-B — Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-011-C — Root package __all__ contents\n\n- **GIVEN** the `agentcube` package\n- **WHEN** `agentcube.__all__` is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-040-011-D — clients subpackage exports\n\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube.clients` is imported\n- **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: CodeInterpreterClient initializes with correct default values\n- [ ] AC002: CodeInterpreterClient reads Router URL from environment when not provided\n- [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreterClient raises ValueError when Router URL is missing\n- [ ] AC004: CodeInterpreterClient context manager creates and cleans up sessions\n- [ ] AC005: CodeInterpreterClient data plane init failure cleans up the created session\n- [ ] AC006: CodeInterpreterClient execute_command and run_code delegate to data plane\n- [ ] AC007: CodeInterpreterClient run_code handles Python language variants\n- [ ] AC008: CodeInterpreterClient file operations delegate to data plane\n- [ ] AC009: ControlPlaneClient resolves URL from argument or environment\n- [ ] AC010: ControlPlaneClient resolves auth token from argument or token file\n- [ ] AC011: ControlPlaneClient create_session POSTs with correct JSON body\n- [ ] AC012: ControlPlaneClient delete_session handles 404 as success\n- [ ] AC013: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs URL from router components\n- [ ] AC014: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient uses explicit base_url when provided\n- [ ] AC015: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient write_file sends base64 content\n- [ ] AC016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient upload_file sends multipart request\n- [ ] AC017: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient download_file streams response\n- [ ] AC018: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient list_files queries with path parameter\n- [ ] AC019: AgentRuntimeClient bootstraps session ID from response header\n- [ ] AC020: AgentRuntimeClient raises when invoking without session\n- [ ] AC021: AgentRuntimeClient invoke sends JSON payload with correct headers\n- [ ] AC022: AgentRuntimeClient uses correct timeout tuple\n- [ ] AC023: CommandExecutionError contains exit_code, stderr, and command\n- [ ] AC024: Exception classes are importable from agentcube root\n- [ ] AC025: create_session returns configured requests.Session\n- [ ] AC026: read_token_from_file handles missing files gracefully\n- [ ] AC027: read_token_from_file returns stripped content\n- [ ] AC028: get_logger returns Logger instance with correct name\n- [ ] AC029: Public API exports correct classes in __all__\n- [ ] AC030: clients subpackage exports correct classes\n\n---\n\n## Test File Status\n\n| Source File | Test File | Status |\n|-------------|-----------|--------|\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | test_init.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | test_code_interpreter.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | test_agent_runtime.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | test_control_plane.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | test_exceptions.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | test_http.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | test_utils.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | test_log.py | **Missing - Needs Implementation** |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Patterns\n\n### Mocking Strategy\n- Use `unittest.mock` for mocking HTTP requests and responses\n- Use `requests_mock` or similar for HTTP server mocking\n- Create fixtures for common client configurations\n\n### Test File Naming\n- Follow Python convention: `test_*.py`\n- Keep tests in `sdk-python/tests/` directory\n- Use `pytest` as test runner\n\n### Test Fixtures\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_control_plane():\n    \"\"\"Fixture for ControlPlaneClient with mocked HTTP\"\"\"\n    ...\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_data_plane():\n    \"\"\"Fixture for CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with mocked HTTP\"\"\"\n    ...\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef sample_session_response():\n    \"\"\"Fixture for session creation response\"\"\"\n    return {\"sessionId\": \"test-session-123\"}\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n- Client initialization: 90%+ coverage\n- Control plane operations: 85%+ coverage\n- Data plane operations: 85%+ coverage\n- Exception handling: 80%+ coverage\n- Utility functions: 90%+ coverage\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- SDK source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/agentcube/`\n- Tests directory: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/tests/`\n- Package: `agentcube-sdk`\n- Dependencies: requests, PyJWT>=2.0.0, cryptography","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883705606,"end":1775883705632}}}}
